CSS cascading stylesheets
selector
declaration block =>property-value pairs

p {
   property: value;
   property: value;
   property: value;
   property: value; 
}

#property - what you want to style
#value - how you want to style

color: red;
font-size: 20px;

p {
    color: blue;
    font-size: 10px;
}

selector => way of targeting html elements to style

How we :target html elements
1. universal selector (*)
* {.....}
2. element selector
forms {....}   
ul {....}
table{....}

3. id selector
<img id="cover-image".src="" alt="">
#cover-image {....}
4. class selector --different types of elements
<div class="main-layout"></div>
<section class="main-layout"></section>
.main-layout {....}

5.group selector
a, p, h1, h2, h3 {....}